# N8N Workflow Rules

## Connection
- N8N config stored at `~/Cursor/shared/configs/n8n-config.json`
- Always read config before making API calls
- Use REST API v1 for all operations

## Workflow Development
- Export workflows to `~/Cursor/projects/n8n-workflows/` for backup
- Name workflows descriptively: `[Category] Action Description`
- Add notes to complex nodes explaining their purpose
- Always include error handling (Error Trigger workflow)

## Best Practices
- Test webhooks locally with curl before deploying
- Use environment variables in n8n for API keys
- Keep workflows focused — use "Execute Workflow" for subroutines
- Pin test data on nodes during development
- Deactivate workflows before making major changes
